**NoUI**

AI-Driven Pension Administration

**Modernize Without Replacing. Deliver Value in Weeks, Not Years.**

*A compelling case for the Denver Employees Retirement Plan*

**Confidential** \| February 2026 \| Prepared for DERP Leadership

**The Challenge You Already Know**

You manage retirement benefits for roughly 28,800 members across three
distinct benefit tiers, each with its own formulas, eligibility rules,
and reduction rates. Your staff navigates legacy screens that were
designed decades ago. Every retirement application requires careful
hand-checking. Every legislative change means months of analysis and
recoding. And when your most experienced staff members retire, their
institutional knowledge walks out the door.

You are not alone. Across the country, public pension systems face the
same compounding pressures:

-   **Legacy systems consume 70--80% of IT budgets** just for
    maintenance, leaving almost nothing for innovation or improvement.

-   **System replacement projects cost \$20--80 million** and fail more
    than half the time. CalPERS abandoned a \$250M modernization effort.
    These are not edge cases; they are the norm.

-   **Institutional knowledge is disappearing** as experienced staff
    retire faster than new analysts can learn systems that lack
    documentation.

-   **Member expectations have shifted.** People expect the same digital
    clarity from their pension as they get from their bank. Legacy
    systems cannot deliver that.

-   **Compliance burden is growing.** GASB requirements, audit
    standards, and legislative changes demand traceability that aging
    systems simply were not built to provide.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **The real cost of the status quo** is not just the IT maintenance
  budget. It is the calculation errors that become liabilities, the staff
  hours lost to workarounds, the member complaints from slow processing,
  and the compliance risk from systems that cannot demonstrate how they
  arrived at a number.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**A Different Approach: Modernize Without Replacing**

NoUI does not ask you to rip out your existing system. Instead, it
connects to your current database, learns your business rules from your
governing documents, and delivers a modern, intelligent workspace to
your staff --- all while your legacy system continues to operate
undisturbed.

**How It Works**

**NoUI reads your governing authority** --- the Revised Municipal Code
of the City and County of Denver, Sections 18-391 through 18-430.7 ---
and drafts rule configurations that are then certified by your subject
matter experts. Every calculation traces directly back to the statute.
This is not a black box; it is the most transparent benefit
administration system available.

The platform operates through four integrated layers:

-   **Data Connector:** Connects to your existing database through
    standard adapters. Your data never leaves your building. NoUI reads
    what it needs and presents it in a clean, modern format.

-   **Business Intelligence:** A rules engine that implements your
    specific plan provisions --- all three DERP tiers, Rule of 75 and
    Rule of 85, early retirement reductions, purchased service, DRO
    calculations --- every rule referenced to its source in the RMC.

-   **Relevance Engine:** Intelligently prioritizes what each staff
    member needs to see for the specific task at hand, while keeping
    everything else accessible. No more hunting through 15--20 screens.

-   **Dynamic Workspace:** Composes a task-specific interface on the
    fly. Processing a Tier 1 Rule of 75 retirement? The workspace shows
    the Rule of 75 calculation, the leave payout impact, and the spousal
    consent requirements. Processing a Tier 3 early retirement?
    Different workspace, different emphasis, same system.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  **Key principle:** AI accelerates configuration and orchestration. AI
  never performs benefit calculations. Every number produced by NoUI
  comes from a deterministic, auditable, version-controlled rules engine.
  Your actuaries and auditors can trace any result from the final dollar
  amount back to the specific RMC section that governs it.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Business Outcomes That Matter**

**1. Accuracy You Can Prove**

Every benefit calculation matches your plan provisions to the penny.
Every formula, every input, every derivation is visible and traceable.
When a board member asks how a particular benefit was calculated, your
staff does not need to reverse-engineer the answer from a legacy system
--- NoUI shows the complete calculation chain: the statute reference,
the member data inputs, the formula applied, and the result.

During the proof of concept, NoUI demonstrates this with four real-world
scenarios drawn from your plan provisions:

-   **A Tier 1 member retiring under Rule of 75** with a leave payout
    that boosts the final benefit, married with a Joint & Survivor
    election.

-   **A Tier 2 member taking early retirement with purchased service**
    --- showing exactly how purchased service counts for the benefit
    formula but is excluded from Rule of 75 eligibility, and how a
    scenario modeler reveals that waiting one year would eliminate the
    early retirement penalty entirely.

-   **A Tier 3 member with the different 60-month AMS window and 6%
    reduction rate,** demonstrating how the system adapts seamlessly
    across tiers.

-   **A DRO case** showing the marital share calculation, percentage
    split, and interaction with payment option elections.

**2. Staff Productivity and Knowledge Preservation**

Your staff currently navigates multiple legacy screens per transaction,
often relying on personal knowledge of which screens to check and in
what order. When experienced analysts retire, that operational
choreography is lost.

NoUI changes this fundamentally. The workspace adapts to the task,
pulling together everything the analyst needs and highlighting what
requires attention. A retirement application that currently requires
checking a dozen screens becomes a single, purpose-built workspace.
Processing times drop. Training time for new staff drops further,
because the system itself embodies institutional knowledge rather than
depending on it living in people's heads.

**3. Proactive Error Detection**

NoUI's data quality engine continuously analyzes your database for
embedded problems that your current system cannot detect: status/date
contradictions, beneficiary allocation errors, contribution balance
mismatches, and other anomalies that accumulate silently over decades.
In the POC, we deliberately seed the demonstration database with
realistic data quality issues --- and show the system finding them
automatically.

For pension plans that have been operating for decades, these embedded
errors represent real financial exposure. Overpayments become
liabilities. Underpayments become legal risk. NoUI surfaces these issues
before they reach a benefit check.

**4. Legislative Change Without the Crisis**

When the Denver City Council amends Sections 18-391 through 18-430.7,
your current response is a multi-month project: analyze the change,
identify affected calculations, modify the legacy system, test, and
deploy. During that gap, you are running on outdated rules or manual
workarounds.

NoUI detects legislative changes, drafts updated rule configurations,
regenerates the full test suite, and presents everything for human
certification --- typically within hours, not months. The annual
platform fee includes this continuous legislative compliance. For
context, many agencies currently spend \$100,000--\$300,000 per year on
legislative change management alone.

**IT Relief: Less Burden, More Capability**

**Your Data Never Leaves Your Building**

NoUI uses a split architecture where AI services operate in the cloud
while your member data stays entirely on-premises, behind your firewall,
under your control. A small Data Connector appliance sits in your data
center and communicates with the NoUI intelligence layer --- but no
personally identifiable information ever transits to the cloud. This is
not a policy or a promise; it is an architectural impossibility for PII
to exist in the cloud environment.

This eliminates entire categories of compliance risk. There is no cloud
data breach scenario to plan for because the data is not there. Your
existing security posture for member data remains intact and unchanged.

**Zero Disruption to Current Operations**

NoUI does not modify, replace, or interfere with your legacy system. It
reads from your existing database through standard connectors. Your
current system continues to operate exactly as it does today. Staff can
use both systems in parallel during transition, and the legacy system
remains the system of record until you decide otherwise.

This means no big-bang cutover, no data migration project, no weekend
outage, no risk of a failed go-live. The system proves itself alongside
your existing operations.

**Progressive Database Modernization --- Included**

Within approximately 12--18 months of normal operation, NoUI delivers a
clean, modern PostgreSQL database as a natural byproduct of its work.
Every transaction it processes builds and validates the modern schema.
There is no separate data conversion project, no data migration weekend,
no reconciliation effort. The modern database simply emerges from
operational use.

A standalone database migration of comparable scope for a plan of DERP's
size would typically cost \$2--5 million as a separate project. With
NoUI, it is included at no additional charge.

**Reduced IT Dependency**

Legacy pension systems create deep IT dependencies: specialized staff
who understand the aging codebase, vendor relationships for platforms
that are approaching end-of-life, and constant firefighting to keep
integrations working. NoUI reduces this dependency by abstracting away
the legacy complexity behind a modern interface and API layer. Your IT
team spends less time maintaining the old system and more time on
initiatives that move the organization forward.

